It is important to highlight that while the above equations are traditionally applied to ART containing reverse-transcriptase inhibitors (RTIs) and protease inhibitors (PIs), treatments including integrase inhibitors (IIs) are also becoming increasingly common. Under II therapy, viral trajectories exhibit three phases of exponential decline that reflect (1) the loss of short-lived productively infected cells; (1b) the loss of short-lived non-productively infected cells; and (2) the loss of long-lived non-productively infected cells [12]. In order to fit such trajectories, we also include a triphasic exponential model given by
